{{cereal}}
[[Image:Wheat in sack.jpg|right|thumb|Wheat in a sack]]

'''Wheat''' is a grain which is the basis of many different kinds of food. Ground into [[Cookbook:Flour|flour]] it is the basis for most of the [[Cookbook:Bread|bread]] and [[Cookbook:Pasta|pasta]] eaten in the world. The whole grains can be boiled and used like rice. With some processing, wheat is converted into [[Cookbook:Couscous|couscous]] and [[Cookbook:Bulgur|bulgur wheat]], which both are easier to cook and used like rice.

Wheat berries (unprocessed seed) are also grown to make [[Cookbook:Wheat grass juice|wheat grass juice]].

