{{Ada/Navigation|Libraries|Ada.Text_IO}}
__TOC__

== The package Text_IO ==

Used for simple [[Ada Programming/Input Output|Input Output]] (IO) in text format.

== Tips and Tricks for Text_IO ==

=== Read a whole line from the console with Ada 95 ===

The <code>Get_Line ()</code> procedure gets a line of text up until the receiving string fills up. If the line is longer than the buffer then you need to read it more than once. The following example from [[Ada Programming/Mathematical calculations|Mathematical calculations]] shows how this is done:

{{Ada/Sourceforge|numeric_4.adb}}

 {{Ada/kw|with}} Ada.Text_IO;
 {{Ada/kw|with}} Ada.Strings.Unbounded;

 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Numeric_4 {{Ada/kw|is}}
   {{Ada/kw|package}} Str {{Ada/kw|renames}} Ada.Strings.Unbounded;
   {{Ada/kw|package}} T_IO {{Ada/kw|renames}} Ada.Text_IO;

 ...

   {{Ada/kw|function}} Get_Line {{Ada/kw|return}} Str.Unbounded_String {{Ada/kw|is}}
      BufferSize : {{Ada/kw|constant}} := 2000;
      Retval     : Str.Unbounded_String := Str.Null_Unbounded_String;
      Item       : String (1 .. BufferSize);
      Last       : Natural;
   {{Ada/kw|begin}}
      Get_Whole_Line :
         {{Ada/kw|loop}}
            T_IO.Get_Line (Item => Item, Last => Last);

            Str.Append (Source => Retval, New_Item => Item (1 .. Last));

            {{Ada/kw|exit}} Get_Whole_Line {{Ada/kw|when}} Last < Item'{{Ada/attribute|Last}};
         {{Ada/kw|end}} {{Ada/kw|loop}} Get_Whole_Line;
         {{Ada/kw|return}} Retval;
   {{Ada/kw|end}} Get_Line;

 ...


Ada 2005 has a function Get_Line which returns a newly created string which contains the whole string.

=== Reading a whole line from a file with Ada 95 ===

In principle it is the same as in console reading but you have to check for the end of file as well:

         {{Ada/kw|exit}} Get_Whole_Line {{Ada/kw|when}} Last < Item'{{Ada/attribute|Last}}
                      {{Ada/kw|or}} IO.End_Of_File (File);

