'''[[:w:Common Lisp|Common Lisp]]''' ('''CL''') is a modern, multi-paradigm, high-performance, compiled, ANSI-standardized, prominent descendant of the long-running family of Lisp programming languages.

The CL Hello World program reads as follows:
 (format t "Hello World!")
